{"insight":"Some truths can only live as you","plainSummary":"The deepest knowing is not a message to repeat, but a life that has been changed.","atAGlance":"Some teachings do not hand us a hidden sentence. They ask whether we have become different. When knowing and becoming are one, comparison by ideas breaks down. We can compare the paths around the change, but not carry the change away as a claim.","match":["person it changed"],"tags":["knowing","change","practice","comparison"]}
